#align(center)[
  #text(size: 20pt, weight: "bold")[What happened to me ?]

  _22th March 2026 - What happened to me ?_
]

\

I'm 22. I'm a student majoring in Computer Science and Machine Learning. I'm graduating this year with high honors. I'm currently an intern at Samsung. Life is good. I drink amazing coffee, work in a glass tower on massive curved screen, hit the gym with great coaches, and eat at delicious restaurants. Indeed, life is good in Big Tech.

\

#align(center)[
_But Something feels off._
]

What happened to the little Lucie ? The one who, at 13, was in love with the Standard Model of particle physics and made a presentation on it ? The one who, at 15, read advanced math and physics books she barely understood ?

She's still here, still asking to unlock the mysteries of the microscopic world.
A few months ago, I made a choice. I want to keep studying.

The easy choice ? The MVA - France's most prestigious master in research in Machine Learning. The master that everyone wants. The master that produces clones.

What about ... The International Master of Physics of Complex Systems ? A highly competitive master in research in physics, relatively unknown to the tech crowd, run by Europe's biggest physics organizations : Sorbonne, Politechnico de Torino, ICTP and SISSA. 
\

#align(center)[
_I applied._
]

One morning at 8AM, I received an email from one of the famouss professor and researcher of the master, asking for a call within 2 hours. He was surprised because I was an CS student and not a physics student. 

He calls me and asks me questions about my background, my motivation, my projects. Little by little, I feel that he's interested. 
'I want to do 8h of physics per day like in preparatory classes' I said at the end of the call and that made him laugh.

\

#align(center)[
_Three weeks laster : I'm accepted._
]

I'm signing up for 2 years of eight hours per day, solving equations with 20 other people and I can't wait.

\

#align(center)[
_So, what exactly is the PCS master ?_ 
]
It's not a random physics master.

It was founded in 2011. Born from a desire of Italian and French researchers to create a program of excellence to train the next generation in the sciences of complexity.
The class take place in 3 different cities : Trieste, Turin and Paris. 

The program is a mix of physics, computer science, mathematics, biology and neurosciences. The students are trained to be able to understand complex systems in all their forms : from the brain to the stock market & quantum mechanics.

The 400 alumni are not randomly distributed in the world. We find them doing postdocs at MIT, Oxbridge, working in big tech, in hedge funds, and top-tier research centers. 

\

#align(center)[
_I am exactly where I'm meant to be._
]

